mobisocial.musubi.model

Class MIncomingSecret

  • java.lang.Object
    • mobisocial.musubi.model.MIncomingSecret

  • public class MIncomingSecret
extends java.lang.Object
    Channel secrets limit the use of public key crypto operations to allow for more sophisticated schemes (IBE) without impacting performance dramatically. The overall stragegy is to lazily cache a unidirectional communication secret key. This allows for one client to speak to another while reusing a shared secret that is implicit to the user.

      • COL_INCOMING_ENCRYPTION_WHEN

        public static final java.lang.String COL_INCOMING_ENCRYPTION_WHEN
        This field stores the specific time that is used to encrypt the message to me. If I haven't fetched my secret from the server for this time, then I will have to. It is different than the signature time period, because the standard expiration times are a function of identity.
